msContents.summary: Mathematical treatise with frequent marginal notes by multiple hands. Some of the marginal notes are textual variants or corrections, sometimes in red and corresponding to red overlining in the text. Later added table of contents (f. i verso-iii recto). Ribbon or thread tied in the outer margin as a marker (f. 118).

msItem.title: Īḍāḥ al-maqāṣid li-farāʼiḍ al-fawāʼid
msItem.author: Kāshī, ʻImād al-Dīn Yaḥyá ibn Aḥmad, d. 1343 or 1344

supportDesc.extent: 172 leaves : 247 x 105 (220 x 75) mm. bound to 247 x 110 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh script by the author (inscription, f. 162r).

decoDesc.decoNote: Occasional small diagrams (for example, f. 97r-99r, 103r-109r, 113r-114v, 136v-142r); overlining and some marginal notes in red.

binding.p: Morocco spine and cover edges, rebacked; panel of parchment or paper and a single gilt stamp on the upper cover; panel now lacking on lower cover; writing on tail-edge.

origin.p: Probably written in Iṣfahān, Iran (Christie's), in A.H. Shaʻbān 720 (September 1320, f. 162r).

history.provenance: Multiple ownership inscriptions (inside upper cover, front flyleaf, f. i recto, 1r); ownership stamps (f. 1r-2r).
Sold at auction at Christie's, 19 April 1999, lot 333, to Lawrence J. Schoenberg.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2013.
